The only thing that is missing is declaring your `NumberRecognizer` as a recognizer supporting Japanese:

```python
money_recognizer = NumbersRecognizer(supported_entities = ['Money'], supported_language="ja")
analyzer.registry.add_recognizer(money_recognizer)
text3 = '￥２０'
numbers_results2 = analyzer.analyze(text = text3, language = 'ja')
print('\n'.join([str(res) for res in numbers_results2]))
```

In Presidio, each recognizer can support only one language. There are two main reasons for this:
1. The input language is defined by the user when calling the `analyze` method, and only recognizers supporting this language are used to serve the request
2. In many cases, the logic for detection is language dependent. For example, context words used in some recognizers are almost always language dependent.

This PR optimizes the Dockerfiles so that the final build image size is reduced. The big size is mostly caused by the `en_core_web_lg` package is being cached on `/root/.cache`. So by adding `ENV PIP_NO_CACHE_DIR=1`, the pip will not cache it anymore, reducing the image size.

I also merge some RUN commands into one RUN, so that it results to 1 layer instead of many layers.

```
                         BEFORE   AFTER
presidio-analyzer        2.1GB    1.26GB
presidio-anonymizer      212MB    196MB
presidio-image-redactor  2.34GB   1.46GB
```

- [ ] My PR contains documentation updates / additions if required

'https://github.com/microsoft/presidio/pull/838.diff', 'patch_url': 'https://github.com/microsoft/presidio/pull/838.patch', 'merged_at': None}, 'body': '## Change Description

This PR optimizes the Dockerfiles so that the final build image size is reduced. The big size is mostly caused by the `en_core_web_lg` package is being cached on `/root/.cache`. So by adding `ENV PIP_NO_CACHE_DIR=1`, the pip will not cache it anymore, reducing the image size.

I also merge some RUN commands into one RUN, so that it results to 1 layer instead of many layers.

```
                         BEFORE   AFTER
presidio-analyzer        2.1GB    1.26GB
presidio-anonymizer      212MB    196MB
presidio-image-redactor  2.34GB   1.46GB
```

When using custom recognizers inheriting from `EntityRecognizer`, the `LemmaContextAwareEnhancer` throws a `TypeError: 'NoneType' object is not subscriptable` due to a missing value within the recognizer result `recognition_metadata` dict.

**To Reproduce**
Steps to reproduce the behavior:
```python
    class MockRecognizer(EntityRecognizer):
        def analyze(self, text: str, entities: List[str], nlp_artifacts: NlpArtifacts):
            return [RecognizerResult("TEST", 50, 60, 0.5)]

    mock_recognizer = MockRecognizer(supported_entities=["TEST"])

    registry = RecognizerRegistry()
    registry.add_recognizer(mock_recognizer)

    analyzer_engine = AnalyzerEngine(registry=registry)
    results = analyzer_engine.analyze("ABC", language="en")
```

**Expected behavior**
NoneType should not be thrown, even if the user didn't pass the recognizer name through the `recognition_metadata` dictionary


Temporary fix:
For each call to `RecognizerRegistry`, add a `recognition_metadta` dict containing {"recognizer_name": "NAME_OF_RECOGNIZER"}.
Example:
```python
result = RecognizerResult(
              entity_type="MY_ENTITY_TYPE"
              start=start,
              end=end,
              score=score,
              recognition_metadata={
                  RecognizerResult.RECOGNIZER_NAME_KEY: self.name

When using custom recognizers inheriting from `EntityRecognizer`, the `LemmaContextAwareEnhancer` throws a `TypeError: 'NoneType' object is not subscriptable` due to a missing value within the recognizer result `recognition_metadata` dict.

**To Reproduce**
Steps to reproduce the behavior:
```python
    class MockRecognizer(EntityRecognizer):
        def analyze(self, text: str, entities: List[str], nlp_artifacts: NlpArtifacts):
            return [RecognizerResult("TEST", 50, 60, 0.5)]

    mock_recognizer = MockRecognizer(supported_entities=["TEST"])

    registry = RecognizerRegistry()
    registry.add_recognizer(mock_recognizer)

    analyzer_engine = AnalyzerEngine(registry=registry)
    results = analyzer_engine.analyze("ABC", language="en")
```

**Expected behavior**
NoneType should not be thrown, even if the user didn't pass the recognizer name through the `recognition_metadata` dictionary


Temporary fix:
For each call to `RecognizerRegistry`, add a `recognition_metadta` dict containing {"recognizer_name": "NAME_OF_RECOGNIZER"}.
Example:
```python
result = RecognizerResult(
              entity_type="MY_ENTITY_TYPE"
              start=start,
              end=end,
              score=score,
              recognition_metadata={
                  RecognizerResult.RECOGNIZER_NAME_KEY: self.name
              })
```', 'reactions': {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/microsoft/presidio/issues/835/reactions', 'total_count': 0, '+1': 0, '-1': 0, 'laugh': 0, 'hooray': 0, 'confused': 0, 'heart': 0, 'rocket': 0, 'eyes': 0}, 'timeline_url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/microsoft/presidio/issues/835/timeline', 'performed_via_github_app': None}}

1. Allow context terms to come from multiple places (before/after a pattern, from the user, from the column name in a tabular data etc.) - by adding context input parameter to ```AnalyzerEngine.analyze()```
2. Allow users to implement their own context logic (not using lemmas, the default we have today) - by creating ```ContextAwareEnhancer```, current logic was extracted from ```EntityRecognizer``` into ```LemmaContextAwareEnhancer``` derived class

Note: current logic inside Phone and Iban Recognizers removed and will be taken care of in a later PR.

Description

1. Allow context terms to come from multiple places (before/after a pattern, from the user, from the column name in a tabular data etc.) - by adding context input parameter to ```AnalyzerEngine.analyze()```
2. Allow users to implement their own context logic (not using lemmas, the default we have today) - by creating ```ContextAwareEnhancer```, current logic was extracted from ```EntityRecognizer``` into ```LemmaContextAwareEnhancer``` derived class

Note: current logic inside Phone and Iban Recognizers removed and will be taken care of in a later PR.

Description

1. Allow context terms to come from multiple places (before/after a pattern, from the user, from the column name in a tabular data etc.) - by adding context input parameter to ```AnalyzerEngine.analyze()```
2. Allow users to implement their own context logic (not using lemmas, the default we have today) - by creating ```ContextAwareEnhancer```, current logic was extracted from ```EntityRecognizer``` into ```LemmaContextAwareEnhancer``` derived class

Note: current logic inside Phone and Iban Recognizers removed and will be taken care of in a later PR.

Description

1. Allow context terms to come from multiple places (before/after a pattern, from the user, from the column name in a tabular data etc.) - by adding context input parameter to ```AnalyzerEngine.analyze()```
2. Allow users to implement their own context logic (not using lemmas, the default we have today) - by creating ```ContextAwareEnhancer```, current logic was extracted from ```EntityRecognizer``` into ```LemmaContextAwareEnhancer``` derived class

Note: current logic inside Phone and Iban Recognizers removed and will be taken care of in a later PR.

Description

1. Allow context terms to come from multiple places (before/after a pattern, from the user, from the column name in a tabular data etc.) - by adding context input parameter to ```AnalyzerEngine.analyze()```
2. Allow users to implement their own context logic (not using lemmas, the default we have today) - by creating ```ContextAwareEnhancer```, current logic was extracted from ```EntityRecognizer``` into ```LemmaContextAwareEnhancer``` derived class

Note: current logic inside Phone and Iban Recognizers removed and will be taken care of in a later PR.

Description

1. Allow context terms to come from multiple places (before/after a pattern, from the user, from the column name in a tabular data etc.) - by adding context input parameter to ```AnalyzerEngine.analyze()```
2. Allow users to implement their own context logic (not using lemmas, the default we have today) - by creating ```ContextAwareEnhancer```, current logic was extracted from ```EntityRecognizer``` into ```LemmaContextAwareEnhancer``` derived class

Note: current logic inside Phone and Iban Recognizers removed and will be taken care of in a later PR.

Description

1. Allow context terms to come from multiple places (before/after a pattern, from the user, from the column name in a tabular data etc.) - by adding context input parameter to ```AnalyzerEngine.analyze()```
2. Allow users to implement their own context logic (not using lemmas, the default we have today) - by creating ```ContextAwareEnhancer```, current logic was extracted from ```EntityRecognizer``` into ```LemmaContextAwareEnhancer``` derived class

Note: current logic inside Phone and Iban Recognizers removed and will be taken care of in a later PR.

Description

1. Allow context terms to come from multiple places (before/after a pattern, from the user, from the column name in a tabular data etc.) - by adding context input parameter to ```AnalyzerEngine.analyze()```
2. Allow users to implement their own context logic (not using lemmas, the default we have today) - by creating ```ContextAwareEnhancer```, current logic was extracted from ```EntityRecognizer``` into ```LemmaContextAwareEnhancer``` derived class

Note: current logic inside Phone and Iban Recognizers removed and will be taken care of in a later PR.

Description

1. Allow context terms to come from multiple places (before/after a pattern, from the user, from the column name in a tabular data etc.) - by adding context input parameter to ```AnalyzerEngine.analyze()```
2. Allow users to implement their own context logic (not using lemmas, the default we have today) - by creating ```ContextAwareEnhancer```, current logic was extracted from ```EntityRecognizer``` into ```LemmaContextAwareEnhancer``` derived class

Note: current logic inside Phone and Iban Recognizers removed and will be taken care of in a later PR.

Description

1. Allow context terms to come from multiple places (before/after a pattern, from the user, from the column name in a tabular data etc.) - by adding context input parameter to ```AnalyzerEngine.analyze()```
2. Allow users to implement their own context logic (not using lemmas, the default we have today) - by creating ```ContextAwareEnhancer```, current logic was extracted from ```EntityRecognizer``` into ```LemmaContextAwareEnhancer``` derived class

Note: current logic inside Phone and Iban Recognizers removed and will be taken care of in a later PR.

+import copy
+import logging
+from typing import List, Optional
+
+from presidio_analyzer import RecognizerResult
+from presidio_analyzer import EntityRecognizer
+from presidio_analyzer.nlp_engine import NlpArtifacts
+from presidio_analyzer.context_aware_enhancers import ContextAwareEnhancer
+
+logger = logging.getLogger("presidio-analyzer")
+
+
+class LemmaContextAwareEnhancer(ContextAwareEnhancer):
+    """
+    A class representing a lemma based context aware enhancer logic.
+
+    Context words might enhance confidence score of a recogized entity,
+    LemmaContextAwareEnhancer is an implementation of Lemma based context aware logic,
+    it compares spacy lemmas of each word in context of the matched entity to given
+    context and the reconizer context words,
+    if matched it enhance the recognized entity confidence score by a given factor.
+
+    :param context_similarity_factor: How much to enhance confidence of match entity
+    :param min_score_with_context_similarity: Minimum confidence score
+    :param context_prefix_count: how many words before the entity to match context
+    :param context_suffix_count: how many words after the entity to match context
+    """
+
+    def __init__(
+        self,
+        context_similarity_factor: float = 0.35,
+        min_score_with_context_similarity: float = 0.4,
+        context_prefix_count: int = 5,
+        context_suffix_count: int = 0,
+    ):
+        super().__init__(
+            context_similarity_factor=context_similarity_factor,
+            min_score_with_context_similarity=min_score_with_context_similarity,
+            context_prefix_count=context_prefix_count,
+            context_suffix_count=context_suffix_count,
+        )
+
+    def enhance_using_context(
+        self,
+        text: str,
+        raw_results: List[RecognizerResult],
+        nlp_artifacts: NlpArtifacts,
+        recognizers: List[EntityRecognizer],
+        context: Optional[List[str]] = None,
+    ) -> List[RecognizerResult]:
+        """
+        Update results in case surrounding words are relevant to the context words.
+
+        Using the surrounding words of the actual word matches, look
+        for specific strings that if found contribute to the score
+        of the result, improving the confidence that the match is
+        indeed of that PII entity type
+
+        :param text: The actual text that was analyzed
+        :param raw_results: Recognizer results which didn't take
+                            context into consideration
+        :param nlp_artifacts: The nlp artifacts contains elements
+                              such as lemmatized tokens for better
+                              accuracy of the context enhancement process
+        :param recognizers: the list of recognizers
+        :param context: list of context words
+        """
+
+        # create a deep copy of the results object so we can manipulate it
+        results = copy.deepcopy(raw_results)
+
+        # create recongnizer context dictionary
+        recognizers_dict = dict()
+        for recognizer in recognizers:
+            recognizers_dict[recognizer.name] = recognizer
+
+        if not context:
+            context = []
+
+        # Sanity
+        if nlp_artifacts is None:
+            logger.warning("[%s]. NLP artifacts were not provided", self.name)
+            return results
+

Description

1. Allow context terms to come from multiple places (before/after a pattern, from the user, from the column name in a tabular data etc.) - by adding context input parameter to ```AnalyzerEngine.analyze()```
2. Allow users to implement their own context logic (not using lemmas, the default we have today) - by creating ```ContextAwareEnhancer```, current logic was extracted from ```EntityRecognizer``` into ```LemmaContextAwareEnhancer``` derived class

Note: current logic inside Phone and Iban Recognizers removed and will be taken care of in a later PR.

Description

1. Allow context terms to come from multiple places (before/after a pattern, from the user, from the column name in a tabular data etc.) - by adding context input parameter to ```AnalyzerEngine.analyze()```
2. Allow users to implement their own context logic (not using lemmas, the default we have today) - by creating ```ContextAwareEnhancer```, current logic was extracted from ```EntityRecognizer``` into ```LemmaContextAwareEnhancer``` derived class

Note: current logic inside Phone and Iban Recognizers removed and will be taken care of in a later PR.

1. Allow context terms to come from multiple places (before/after a pattern, from the user, from the column name in a tabular data etc.) - by adding context input parameter to ```AnalyzerEngine.analyze()```

Note: current logic inside Phone and Iban Recognizers removed and will be taken care of in a later PR.

Description

1. Allow context terms to come from multiple places (before/after a pattern, from the user, from the column name in a tabular data etc.) - by adding context input parameter to ```AnalyzerEngine.analyze()```
2. Allow users to implement their own context logic (not using lemmas, the default we have today) - by creating ```ContextAwareEnhancer```, current logic was extracted from ```EntityRecognizer``` into ```LemmaContextAwareEnhancer``` derived class

Description

1. Allow context terms to come from multiple places (before/after a pattern, from the user, from the column name in a tabular data etc.) - by adding context input parameter to ```AnalyzerEngine.analyze()```
2. Allow users to implement their own context logic (not using lemmas, the default we have today) - by creating ```ContextAwareEnhancer```, current logic was extracted from ```EntityRecognizer``` into ```LemmaContextAwareEnhancer``` derived class

Note: current logic inside Phone and Iban Recognizers removed and will be taken care of in a later PR.

+class LemmaContextAwareEnhancer(ContextAwareEnhancer):
+    """

+
+    Context words might enhance confidence score of a recogized entity,
+    LemmaContextAwareEnhancer is an implementation of Lemma based context aware logic,
+    it compares spacy lemmas of each word in context of the matched entity to given
+    context and the reconizer context words,
+    if matched it enhance the recognized entity confidence score by a given factor.
+

+    :param context_suffix_count: how many words after the entity to match context

+
+    def __init__(
+        self,
+        context_similarity_factor: float = 0.35,
+        min_score_with_context_similarity: float = 0.4,
+        context_prefix_count: int = 5,
+        context_suffix_count: int = 0,
+    ):
+        super().__init__(
+            context_similarity_factor=context_similarity_factor,
+            min_score_with_context_similarity=min_score_with_context_similarity,
+            context_prefix_count=context_prefix_count,
+            context_suffix_count=context_suffix_count,

+        context: Optional[List[str]] = None,
+    ) -> List[RecognizerResult]:
+        """
+        Update results in case surrounding words are relevant to the context words.
+
+        Using the surrounding words of the actual word matches, look
+        for specific strings that if found contribute to the score
+        of the result, improving the confidence that the match is
+        indeed of that PII entity type
+
+        :param text: The actual text that was analyzed
+        :param raw_results: Recognizer results which didn't take
+                            context into consideration
+        :param nlp_artifacts: The nlp artifacts contains elements
+                              such as lemmatized tokens for better
+                              accuracy of the context enhancement process
+        :param recognizers: the list of recognizers
+        :param context: list of context words
+        """
+
+        # create a deep copy of the results object so we can manipulate it
+        results = copy.deepcopy(raw_results)
+
+        # create recongnizer context dictionary
+        recognizers_dict = dict()
+        for recognizer in recognizers:
+            recognizers_dict[recognizer.name] = recognizer
+
+        if not context:
+            context = []
+
+        # Sanity
+        if nlp_artifacts is None:
+            logger.warning("[%s]. NLP artifacts were not provided", self.name)
+            return results
+
+        for result in results:
+            # get recognizer matching the result
+            recognizer = recognizers_dict[result.recognizer_name]
+            if recognizer.context is None or recognizer.context == []:
+                logger.debug(
+                    "recognizer '%s' does not support context enhancement",
+                    recognizer.name,
+                )
+            else:
+                # combine other sources of context with recognizer context
+                context.extend(recognizer.context)
+
+            # extract lemmatized context from the surrounding of the match
+            if len(context) > 0:
+                word = text[result.start : result.end]
+
+                surrounding_words = self.__extract_surrounding_words(
+                    nlp_artifacts=nlp_artifacts, word=word, start=result.start
+                )
+
+                supportive_context_word = self.__find_supportive_word_in_context(
+                    surrounding_words, context
+                )
+                if supportive_context_word != "":
+                    result.score += self.context_similarity_factor
+                    result.score = max(
+                        result.score, self.min_score_with_context_similarity
+                    )
+                    result.score = min(result.score, ContextAwareEnhancer.MAX_SCORE)
+
+                    # Update the explainability object with context information
+                    # helped improving the score
+                    result.analysis_explanation.set_supportive_context_word(
+                        supportive_context_word
+                    )
+                    result.analysis_explanation.set_improved_score(result.score)
+        return results
+

Description

1. Allow context terms to come from multiple places (before/after a pattern, from the user, from the column name in a tabular data etc.) - by adding context input parameter to ```AnalyzerEngine.analyze()```
2. Allow users to implement their own context logic (not using lemmas, the default we have today) - by creating ```ContextAwareEnhancer```, current logic was extracted from ```EntityRecognizer``` into ```LemmaContextAwareEnhancer``` derived class

Note: current logic inside Phone and Iban Recognizers removed and will be taken care of in a later PR.

Description

1. Allow context terms to come from multiple places (before/after a pattern, from the user, from the column name in a tabular data etc.) - by adding context input parameter to ```AnalyzerEngine.analyze()```
2. Allow users to implement their own context logic (not using lemmas, the default we have today) - by creating ```ContextAwareEnhancer```, current logic was extracted from ```EntityRecognizer``` into ```LemmaContextAwareEnhancer``` derived class

Note: current logic inside Phone and Iban Recognizers removed and will be taken care of in a later PR.
